ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
POLL REFEREES: Rep. Robert K. Dornan, a veteran monitor of seven foreign 
elections, says independent observers can make or break public confidence in 
election results. . . . In Panama and in the Philippines, U.S. observers' 
reports of widespread fraud led to governments' being overturned, he noted. Now 
awaiting permission to enter Nicaragua for Sunday's elections, Dornan says: 
"The only thing more enjoyable than voting yourself is to watch other people 
vote when it gives them freedom for the first time."A16 Dana Parsons and 
Kristina Lindgren 
